25|$|Air Tanzania {{restarted}} {{operations to}} Kigoma on 10 January 2013, by using its Bombardier Q300. The airline quickly expanded to domestic routes and even began {{to fly to}} <b>Bujumbura</b> under new management.|$|E
25|$|An {{epidemic}} of cholera rages in <b>Bujumbura,</b> {{the capital of}} Burundi. On 20 January, a United Nations executive announced that 105 people were infected and that 5 deaths had been recorded.|$|E
